<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[5,1880,92,1170]" pageId="20" pageNumber="273" type="mainText">Dwarf shrubs. Leaf blades insignificant; sclereids absent in the chlorenchyma. Flowers in triads in the axil of opposite, usually connate bracts, bisexual or rarely pistillate; perianth 3-lobed; stamen 1, abaxial. Seed coat membranous to crustaceous; embryo curved perisperm present, lateral. Twenty three spp., Australia, rarely S Asia.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
